# Accessibility Patterns

Build interfaces that work for everyone - keyboard users, screen reader users, and users with various disabilities.

## Default Behavior

### Use Semantic HTML First

Native HTML elements have built-in accessibility. Only add ARIA when semantic HTML isn't sufficient.

```html
<!-- ✅ Default: Semantic HTML -->
<button type="button" (click)="onSave()">Save</button>
<nav aria-label="Main navigation">...</nav>
<main>...</main>
<article>...</article>

<!-- ❌ Avoid: Divs with ARIA roles when semantic exists -->
<div role="button" (click)="onSave()">Save</div>
```

### Label All Interactive Elements

Every interactive element must have an accessible name.

```html
<!-- ✅ Default: Visible label -->
<label for="email">Email</label>
<input id="email" type="email" />

<!-- ✅ Default: aria-label for icon-only buttons -->
<button type="button" aria-label="Delete item" (click)="onDelete()">
  <svg aria-hidden="true"><!-- icon --></svg>
</button>

<!-- ✅ Default: sr-only for visually hidden labels -->
<label for="search" class="sr-only">Search users</label>
<input id="search" type="search" placeholder="Search..." />
```

### Announce Dynamic Content

Use `aria-live` regions for content that updates without page reload.

```html
<!-- ✅ Default: Polite announcements for non-urgent updates -->
<div aria-live="polite">
  Showing {{ count() }} of {{ total() }} results
</div>

<!-- ✅ Default: Assertive for errors -->
<div role="alert" aria-live="assertive">
  @if (error()) {
    {{ error() }}
  }
</div>
```

### Support Keyboard Navigation

Interactive elements must be keyboard accessible.

```html
<!-- ✅ Default: Keyboard support on clickable elements -->
<article 
  class="card"
  tabindex="0"
  role="button"
  [attr.aria-pressed]="selected()"
  (click)="onSelect()"
  (keydown.enter)="onSelect()"
  (keydown.space)="onSelect()"
>
  ...
</article>
```

### Visible Focus Indicators

Never remove focus without replacement.

```scss
// ✅ Default: Clear focus indicators
:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--focus-color, #005fcc);
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

// ✅ Custom focus for specific elements
.btn:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid var(--primary-color);
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 4px rgba(0, 95, 204, 0.2);
}
```

## Rationale

1. **Legal compliance** - WCAG 2.1 AA is required in many jurisdictions.
2. **Broader reach** - ~15% of users have some form of disability.
3. **Better UX for all** - Keyboard shortcuts, clear focus states, and structured content benefit everyone.

## Documented Exceptions

### 1. Decorative Images Skip Alt Text

Images that are purely decorative should be hidden from screen readers.

```html
<!-- ✅ Exception: Decorative image -->
<img src="decorative-wave.svg" alt="" aria-hidden="true" />

<!-- ✅ Exception: Icon alongside text -->
<button>
  <svg aria-hidden="true"><!-- icon --></svg>
  Save Changes
</button>
```

### 2. Skip aria-live for User-Initiated Actions

Don't announce changes the user directly caused through their action.

```html
<!-- ❌ Unnecessary: User clicked delete, they know it was deleted -->
<div aria-live="polite">Item deleted</div>

<!-- ✅ Exception: Only announce unexpected or async results -->
<div aria-live="polite">
  @if (searchResults().length === 0) {
    No results found for "{{ searchTerm() }}"
  }
</div>
```

### 3. Complex Widgets May Require Custom Keyboard Patterns

Standard ARIA patterns for menus, dialogs, and trees have specific keyboard expectations.

```typescript
// ✅ Exception: Custom keyboard handling for dropdown menu
@HostListener('keydown', ['$event'])
onKeydown(event: KeyboardEvent) {
  switch (event.key) {
    case 'ArrowDown':
      this.focusNextItem();
      event.preventDefault();
      break;
    case 'ArrowUp':
      this.focusPreviousItem();
      event.preventDefault();
      break;
    case 'Escape':
      this.close();
      break;
  }
}
```

## Anti-Patterns

```html
<!-- ❌ No label -->
<input type="text" placeholder="Enter name" />

<!-- ❌ Placeholder as label (disappears on input) -->
<input type="email" placeholder="Email" />

<!-- ❌ Click handler on non-interactive element without keyboard -->
<div (click)="doSomething()">Click me</div>

<!-- ❌ Removing focus outline without replacement -->
button:focus { outline: none; }

<!-- ❌ aria-live on everything -->
<div aria-live="polite">
  <ul>
    @for (item of items(); track item.id) {
      <li>{{ item.name }}</li>  <!-- Announces EVERY item change -->
    }
  </ul>
</div>

<!-- ❌ Generic link text -->
<a href="/more">Click here</a>
<a href="/docs">Read more</a>
```

## Screen Reader Only Utility

Include in global styles:

```scss
.sr-only {
  position: absolute;
  width: 1px;
  height: 1px;
  padding: 0;
  margin: -1px;
  overflow: hidden;
  clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0);
  white-space: nowrap;
  border: 0;
}

// Allow element to be focusable (for skip links)
.sr-only-focusable:focus {
  position: static;
  width: auto;
  height: auto;
  margin: 0;
  overflow: visible;
  clip: auto;
  white-space: normal;
}
```

## Complete Form Field Pattern

```html
<div class="form-field">
  <label for="email">
    Email
    <span aria-hidden="true" class="required">*</span>
  </label>
  <input
    id="email"
    type="email"
    formControlName="email"
    [attr.aria-invalid]="isInvalid('email')"
    [attr.aria-describedby]="getDescribedBy('email')"
    autocomplete="email"
  />
  <span id="email-hint" class="hint">
    We'll never share your email
  </span>
  @if (isInvalid('email')) {
    <span id="email-error" class="error" role="alert">
      Please enter a valid email address
    </span>
  }
</div>
```

```typescript
getDescribedBy(field: string): string {
  const parts = [`${field}-hint`];
  if (this.isInvalid(field)) {
    parts.push(`${field}-error`);
  }
  return parts.join(' ');
}
```

## Modal Focus Management

```typescript
// ✅ Default: Focus first element when modal opens
ngOnInit() {
  this.previousFocus = document.activeElement as HTMLElement;
  this.focusFirstElement();
}

// ✅ Default: Restore focus when modal closes
ngOnDestroy() {
  this.previousFocus?.focus();
}
```

## Loading States

```html
<!-- ✅ Accessible loading indicator -->
<div [attr.aria-busy]="isLoading()">
  @if (isLoading()) {
    <div class="spinner" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <span class="sr-only">Loading content, please wait...</span>
  } @else {
    <!-- Content -->
  }
</div>
```

## Motion and Animation

```scss
// ✅ Respect user preferences
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  *,
  *::before,
  *::after {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    animation-iteration-count: 1 !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
}
```

## Color & Contrast

Minimum contrast ratios (WCAG AA):
- Normal text: 4.5:1
- Large text (18pt+): 3:1
- UI components: 3:1

## ARIA Quick Reference

| Attribute | Use For |
|-----------|---------|
| `aria-label` | Labels when no visible text |
| `aria-labelledby` | Points to visible label element |
| `aria-describedby` | Additional context (hints, errors) |
| `aria-invalid="true"` | Field has validation error |
| `aria-live="polite"` | Dynamic content updates |
| `aria-live="assertive"` | Urgent updates (errors) |
| `aria-busy="true"` | Content is loading |
| `aria-pressed="true"` | Toggle button state |
| `aria-expanded="true"` | Expandable content state |
| `aria-hidden="true"` | Hide from screen readers |
| `role="alert"` | Important messages |
| `role="status"` | Status updates |

## Testing Checklist

- [ ] Keyboard navigation works for all interactive elements
- [ ] Focus order is logical
- [ ] Focus is visible on all interactive elements
- [ ] All images have alt text (or aria-hidden if decorative)
- [ ] Form fields have associated labels
- [ ] Error messages are announced
- [ ] Color is not the only way to convey information
- [ ] Text can be resized to 200% without loss of content
- [ ] Page works with screen reader (NVDA, VoiceOver)
